\n\nC: quick correct decisions (decision-making), concern for others (teamwork), excellent attention (cognitive). Negatives: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education (professional development). Egocentric may affect teamwork. Lack of development is a concern for long-term.\n\nD: responds to unexpected events adequately (calmness), concentration, problem solving, responsibility (reliability). Negatives: moody, loner (teamwork). No explicit technical flight skills like weather, spatial vision. But problem solving and concentration are good.\n\nThus best seems B: strong reliability, stress handling, technical weather assessment, conscientious, but communication tone issues. However B's communication issues may be mitigated? But we cannot mitigate; we must weigh as evidence. B's negatives are pretentiousness and wrong tone, which affect crew cooperation. C also has communication difficulty and egocentric, plus unwillingness to develop. D has moody and loner, which also affect teamwork. A is unfriendly and unhealthy.\n\nWhich candidate has the least severe negatives? B's pretentiousness and tone may be less severe than egocentric, unwillingness to develop, moody loner, unfriendly unhealthy. B's positives are strong across many criteria. So B likely best.\n\nThus vote for Candidate B.\n\nWe should also note any uncertainties: we lack info on A's stress handling, D's technical flight skills, etc. But based on available, B seems best.\n\nNow produce output."}
